roguesquatcher They have cut there Defense Budget by about 6% but have managed to keep up there spending on new key developments in the Missile area. The key areas. There new Hypersonic Missiles going into full production this year are a game changer. They virtually will cripple the US Navy and they dont need new aircraft or stealth aircraft to deliver them. They also dont need stealth Aircraft to defend against the US Airforce. Are you aware they have about 1250 S400 and S300 SAMs active. All mobile and easy to conceal and set up in less than 30mins. Sure they are primarily defensive but in the case of Russian ground forces going on the attack they will move with them allowing them to operate without fear of Air strikes. You dont have to have fighters. As your troops move forward you move your SAMs up behind your troops giving them cover from aircraft up to 400km out. US and NATO stand off weapons simply dont have the range to stay outside that range. 
There also is no doubt all the S400 plus updated S300 can pick up and target Stealth aircraft using VHF for mid-course guidance.
They also have about 1,000 older S300 in reserve plus thousands of shorter range SAMs. 
The one reason why Development of systems like the S500 is not affected is they are making large profits out of selling other systems. That funds the research. Not all the funding for research comes from the Russian Government. 
I would point out now Oil prices are rising with the cuts to Russian spending they no longer are drawing on there reserves. They actually are operating at a Government level with a surplus if you take into account Russia is still increasing there Gold Reserves. Gold is as good if not better than money in the bank. Get some true facts.
